ch.obermuhlner.jhuge.collection

Class ImmutableHugeHashSet<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractSet<E>
        • ch.obermuhlner.jhuge.collection.AbstractHugeHashSet<E>
          • ch.obermuhlner.jhuge.collection.ImmutableHugeHashSet<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Set<E>

    public class ImmutableHugeHashSet<E>
extends AbstractHugeHashSet<E>
    An immutable Set that stores elements in a MemoryManager.

    The mutating operations throw UnsupportedOperationException:

    • AbstractCollection.add(Object)
    • AbstractCollection.addAll(Collection)
    • AbstractCollection.remove(Object)
    • AbstractSet.removeAll(Collection)
    • AbstractCollection.clear()
    • Iterator.remove() when iterating over this collection
      • s *

    In order to create an ImmutableHugeHashSet you must add the elements in the ImmutableHugeHashSet.Builder.

    Other than the mutating operations all semantics, memory consumption and performance are identical to HugeHashSet.

    See Also:
    HugeHashSet
